title: Virginia Girls Win Second Straight 7A Title
text:
Virginia Girls Win Second Straight 7A Title 
By Zach Schneider Virginia Girls Win Second Straight 7A Title October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 9:46 PM CDT 
Virginia, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The Virginia girls' tennis team beat Duluth Marshall 5-2 on Monday afternoon in the Section 7A championship, earning the Blue Devils a second straight trip to the MSHSL Class A tournament. 
Anna Seitz and Ava Warren both won singles matches for Virginia, while the doubles pairings of Jill Westerbur/Callie Mauston, Cassie Cornell/Alex Saxhaug, and Grace Paulsen/Amelia Cope-Robinson all won as well the Blue Devils. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Duluth Marshall's wins both came in singles, with Nore Heinitz and Azalea Ginete earning the victories. 
It's Virginia's eighth trip to the state tournament in the past nine years, with the competition set to start on Oct. 27.
